			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2385993">
									

<p>Personally, I interpret the boy to be the man who would become the in-universe &quot;The Administrator&quot; or a founder of the Foundation. Without him, there would be no Foundation.</p>
<p>Of course, such an interpretation leans towards Great Man history&#8230; but there are some institutions that are ultimately the works of individuals. If not for Genghis Khan, there would be no &quot;Mongols&quot;. Even if another warlord united the would-be Mongols, they may not necessarily be the Mongols we know in history.</p>

